This did get me thinking. Some of Elephant's general statements bothered me, as it sounded as if they applied to a reality larger than the one in the book.

Last question is a poor use of language, and therefore can be taken either as:
1) Is it true that every (lion?) opted not to buy a cookie? ...or
2) Is it true that not every lion bought a cookie?

So, could be either definitely no, or definitely yes. Can't really determine.

Also, some questions heavily implied a definite answer, but never explicitly stated it, so had to adjust the confidence level accordingly.

Perhaps this is part of the experiment?

In any event, I enjoyed this one. Thanks!
